1
00:00:05,160 --> 00:00:08,420
Have you ever had to read through a really long document and summarize the key points?

2
00:00:08,900 --> 00:00:10,860
Well, now you can ask a chatbot to do that for you.

3
00:00:11,280 --> 00:00:14,580
Now let's take a look at one of these synthesized tasks called summarization.

4
00:00:15,860 --> 00:00:20,160
Text summarization can really help you speed up your learning or help you when you're researching

5
00:00:20,320 --> 00:00:25,520
a topic to really extract the parts of an article or document that's most relevant to what you're

6
00:00:25,620 --> 00:00:25,940
looking for.

7
00:00:26,560 --> 00:00:29,200
So let's look at an example where you might use summarization.

8
00:00:29,460 --> 00:00:32,580
Let's say you want to learn about Banksy from a Wikipedia article.

9
00:00:33,280 --> 00:00:37,840
It's quite long, and you may want to focus on a specific subtopic within the article.

10
00:00:38,260 --> 00:00:39,740
So how can you ask a chatbot to help?

11
00:00:40,500 --> 00:00:45,120
One thing you can try is to give the chatbot a web link and then ask it to summarize the article.

12
00:00:45,600 --> 00:00:49,080
And in this case, I'm going to have it focus on a specific subtopic,

13
00:00:49,380 --> 00:00:55,160
which is to summarize Banksy's activities that relate to social, geopolitical, or current events.

14
00:00:55,760 --> 00:01:02,560
Let's use Notebook LM by Google, which is a tool that lets you upload documents and then chat about them using Gemini.

15
00:01:03,040 --> 00:01:08,040
You can start by clicking the button "Create" and you can see there are a couple options for uploading documents.

16
00:01:08,460 --> 00:01:14,300
You can connect it to Google Drive, you can paste the text in directly, you can upload documents in PDF or text format,

17
00:01:14,680 --> 00:01:18,920
and it also has the option for you to provide a link to a website. Let's use the website option.

18
00:01:19,760 --> 00:01:23,680
Again, here's the Wikipedia article, so you can copy the web link and paste it in here.

19
00:01:23,980 --> 00:01:27,920
I'm fast forwarding a bit, but it takes a few seconds to process the website.

20
00:01:28,360 --> 00:01:32,060
